stimulus:
Welcome to the experiment!

Please note that headphones are required for this experiment, and that background noise will make the task difficult.
If you haven't done so already, please put on headphones and move to a quiet environment.

Then, press the space bar to begin.

First, we'll go through a quick exercise to make sure you're wearing headphones.

Set your volume at 20%, then press the space bar to continue.

In each of the following trials, you will hear three sounds separated by silence.

Your task is to judge which sound was the SOFTEST - 1, 2, or 3.

Please note that test sounds will only play once.

Press the space bar to continue.

Great! You passed the headphone check.

Press the space bar to continue.

Now, it's time for the experiment.

In each of the following trials, you will hear an audio track that consists of one or more musicians, each playing a single instrument.

Your task is to report how many musicians you hear playing.

Each track will only play once!

Press the space bar to continue.

Thank you! We have one more task for you.

Each of the following sets of audio clips feature two musicians playing.

Your task is to choose which of the three clips does not sound the same as the other two.

Ready? Press the space bar to continue.

Please listen to these three audio mixes:

And select which file is not like the other two.

Please listen to these three audio mixes:

And select which file is not like the other two.
